Title: Path Integral for the Dirac Equation
Author: Janos Polonyi
Comments: 4 pages, uses sprocl.sty, talk delivered at the the conference
  "Path-integrals from peV to TeV", Florence, August, 1998
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B453 (1999) 40-45
\\
  A path integral representation is given for the solutions of the 3+1
dimensional Dirac equation. The regularity of the trajectories, the
non-relativistic limit and the semiclassical approximation are briefly
mentioned.
